shared_text:
Rotary Club of Norristown
July 14 at 5:55 AM ·

The Rotary Club of Norristown grieves the passing of former member, Dr. James N. Holton last Friday, July 10th of Cassadaga N.Y.,
Jim's hometown was Norristown. He attended AD Eisenhower HS before spending 32 years in public education including serving as Superintendent of the Norristown Area School Dictrict. He was an active Norristown Rotary member during this time and he served as Club President from 2003-2004. After retirement, he and his wife moved to Cassadaga N.Y. where they remained active in music, public service and Rotary. We all miss Jim and we extend our condolences to his wife Mary and their family.

https://www.post-journal.com/obituaries/2020/07/james-n-holton-2/

shared_text:
Montgomery County OIC
April 16 at 2:10 PM ·

OIC is pleased to partner with the Norristown Area School District to have education packets available this Friday, April 17th from 4:00 PM to 6:00 PM. If you are in a household without access to a chromebook or computer access to complete the work, you can come to the OIC parking lot and pick up a packet for your child. Please help us stop the spread by maintaining social distancing guidelines. We are located at 1101 Arch Street in Norristown. Enter the parking lot from Basin Street. We have packets available for all schools for regular education, special education, ELD/ESL, core high school classes, and specialty high school classes.

NOTICE IS HEREBY GIVEN THAT the Norristown Area School District Board of School Directors has scheduled a Regular Voting Meeting for March 23, 2020, at 7:00 PM. Since all school facilities are currently closed by the order of the Governor of Pennsylvania, the advertised meeting will be conducted virtually to allow for public participation despite the current restrictions in place regarding mass gatherings. Members of the public wishing to participate may join the meeting via the internet or by phone. Please use the following information to participate:
Please use the following URL to join via internet-capable device: https://zoom.us/j/161130677

You can call either phone number listed below to join the meeting by phone: 1-646-558-8656 or 1-312-626-6799.

Meeting ID # is 161 130 677.

Anyone wishing to sign up for public comment is asked to email the Superintendent prior to the start of the meeting at cdormer@nasd.k12.pa.us. Please include your name, address, phone number, and any affiliation in the email.

post_text: Help us congratulate Dr. Lelli on her Norristown Area High School Hall of Fame induction! #NASDProud #BeTheLeader
shared_text:
Collegeville Italian Bakery Pizzeria Napoletana
November 12, 2019 at 9:13 PM ·

Our Pizzaioli of the Day is Dr. Colleen Lelli!

Dr. Lelli is an associate professor of education at Cabrini University and a pillar in her community. She serves as co-president of the board for the Laurel House and also serves on the boards of the Royersford Library and the Delaware County Women Against Rape.

This Thursday, Dr. Lelli will be inducted into the Norristown Area High School Hall of Fame.

Dr. Lelli’s past and present students greatly respect and admire her. Her tireless dedication to helping others in the surrounding communities is impacting families on a daily basis. She is an amazing person!

Congratulations on this well-deserved honor, Dr. Lelli!
